Moreover, the projective variety &quot;X&quot; is an algebraic variety, meaning that it is covered by open affine subvarieties and satisfies the separation axiom. Thus, the local study of &quot;X&quot; (e.g., singularity) reduces to that of an affine variety. The explicit structure is as follows. The projective space formula_1 is covered by the standard open affine charts

