Projections can be used to cut down the dimension in which a projective variety is embedded, up to finite morphisms. Start with some projective variety formula_117 If formula_118 the projection from a point not on &quot;X&quot; gives formula_119 Moreover, formula_120 is a finite map to its image. Thus, iterating the procedure, one sees there is a finite map

