For each &quot;L&quot;, the construction is a bijection between the set of &quot;L&quot;-points of formula_124 and the set of hyperplanes on formula_127. Because of this, the dual projective space formula_124 is said to be the moduli space of hyperplanes on formula_39.

A line in formula_124 is called a pencil: it is a family of hyperplanes on formula_39 parametrized by formula_137.

If &quot;V&quot; is a finite-dimensional vector space over &quot;k&quot;, then, for the same reason as above, formula_138 is the space of hyperplanes on formula_139. An important case is when &quot;V&quot; consists of sections of a line bundle. Namely, let &quot;X&quot; be an algebraic variety, &quot;L&quot; a line bundle on &quot;X&quot; and formula_140 a vector subspace of finite positive dimension. Then there is a map:

