As a corollary to 1. above, if &quot;f&quot; is a projective morphism from a noetherian scheme to a noetherian ring, then the higher direct image formula_155 is coherent. The same result holds for proper morphisms &quot;f&quot;, as can be shown with the aid of Chow&#x27;s lemma.

Sheaf cohomology groups &quot;Hi&quot; on a noetherian topological space vanish for &quot;i&quot; strictly greater than the dimension of the space. Thus the quantity, called the Euler characteristic of formula_145,

